Comparative activity of cefepime, alone and in combination, against clinical isolates of Pseudomonas aeruginosa and Pseudomonas cepacia from cystic fibrosis patients.
 The comparative in vitro activity and synergy of cefepime were evaluated with clinical isolates of Pseudomonas aeruginosa and Pseudomonas cepacia from cystic fibrosis patients.
 The activity of cefepime, both alone and in combination, was comparable to those of other antibiotics.
 The clinical efficacy of cefepime in cystic fibrosis patients merits investigation.
